Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.53,0:01:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Teddy, where were you?"
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.49,0:01:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"I took a puzzle and sat on the street waiting for you."
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.62,0:01:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"What? I told you to wait with the bamboo seller!"
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.58,0:01:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, I thought you said 'with a bamboozler'."
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.58,0:01:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your continued appreciation.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.63,0:01:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:48.46,0:01:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a good...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.59,0:01:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,year...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.84,0:01:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,everybo...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:52.13,0:01:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,...dy.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.05,0:01:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's a running gag at this point, \Nso I'll just keep quiet.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.72,0:01:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:59.27,0:02:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not pull this crap at Valentine's.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.31,0:02:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy new year!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.40,0:02:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what was everyone's first dream of the year?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.99,0:02:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask such dull—
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.90,0:02:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask such horrible questions!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.91,0:02:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to relive the good old times, and yet...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.91,0:02:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's horrible about it?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.28,0:02:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't had one yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:19.83,0:02:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been able to sleep since New Year's Eve.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.04,0:02:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't had a New Year's dream yet!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:23.96,0:02:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.83,0:02:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You go ahead and discuss your dreams!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.50,0:02:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave me out because I didn't have one!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.30,0:02:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I bet you all had {\i1}breathtaking{\i0} dreams!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.59,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realise she had such an inferiority complex.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.84,0:02:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe 'cuz she hasn't slept.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.26,0:02:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A-All right then, Kukuru.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.31,0:02:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you sleep here?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.97,0:02:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, just close your eyes...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.64,0:02:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll sing you a lullaby.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.60,0:02:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep... go to sleep...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:56.66,0:02:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm being cursed.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.91,0:03:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry! We'll stop.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.33,0:03:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a life hack for ya!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.87,0:03:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You count one lamb, two lambs, three lambs...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.33,0:03:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely "sheep" would work a lot better for that.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.79,0:03:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sheep" and "sleep" sound very similar,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.46,0:03:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's like you're hypnotising yourself to sleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.42,0:03:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay then, just say "sheep one, sheep two".
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.43,0:03:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't they be plural?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.09,0:03:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the plural of sheep?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.72,0:03:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}To make something plural in English, \Nyou just slap on an {\i1}s{\i0} at the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.14,0:03:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The plural of "sheep" is "sheep".
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.27,0:03:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,For freaking real?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.31,0:03:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Sheep are treated as a flock, \Nso the noun is uncountable.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.11,0:03:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Have they never seen a sheep on its own?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.11,0:03:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't sl{/h}eep with all this noise.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.73,0:03:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay, we'll try to keep it down.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.55,0:03:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I may not be able to sleep, but I see \Nthat isn't stopping you all from having fun.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.14,0:03:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.51,0:04:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You early dreamers go ahead and enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.56,0:04:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I get to have is this unending torment!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.60,0:04:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}As the year turned, the old stray that \Nused to visit every day stopped coming by.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.65,0:04:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}My father suddenly announced that he \Nwas going to get a licence for dealing antiques,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.99,0:04:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}seemingly convinced he was \Ngoing to be laid off from his company.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.99,0:04:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}My grandmother started wearing more \Nand more make-up, often leaving the house.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.99,0:04:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't uncommon for her to stay out all night.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.83,0:04:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}In the end, a white Republican man who claimed to \Nhave been an acquaintance of my mother's
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.63,0:04:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,invited us to go live with him in Oregon.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.05,0:04:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The start of the year brings nothing but pain!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.09,0:04:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I just want to dream! \NIs that so much to ask?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.30,0:04:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough drama for one of those cellphone novels.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.22,0:04:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever happened to those?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.31,0:04:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Don't worry! Even people with insomnia \Ndon't go that long without sleeping.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.98,0:04:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.06,0:04:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You get people who say they haven't slept in five days, \Nbut usually they dozed off a little without realising it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.03,0:05:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.82,0:05:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If your insomnia persists, things get hazy
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.87,0:05:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}and you stop being able to tell \Nwhere dreams end and reality begins.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.70,0:05:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I wish it had all been a dream! \NThe cat, my father, my grandmother, and Oregon!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.33,0:05:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez. This is getting tiresome.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.00,0:05:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What if this is all a dream?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.71,0:05:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Being backstage, being turned into an anime... \NIt could be, you know!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.22,0:05:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Now that you mention it, that bamboo ornament \Nthat crashed through the wall was too big to be realistic.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:24.97,0:05:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.64,0:05:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey now, this is definitely reality.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.64,0:05:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you say stuff like that, \Nyou're setting yourself up for—
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.81,0:05:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got an idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.77,0:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give Kukuru her first dream of the year!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.02,0:05:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly feel like this might be a dream!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.57,0:05:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}She's no longer able to tell \Nthe difference between dreams and reality.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.32,0:05:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We can make sure she has a wonderful dream!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.91,0:05:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is definitely a dream!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.03,0:05:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's our chance!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.62,0:05:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to put on a dream play.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.66,0:05:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We're backstage now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.37,0:05:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A backstage inside the backstage.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.25,0:05:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a dream within a dream!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.38,0:06:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Let's act out an amazing New Year's dream \Nand make Kukuru happy again!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.30,0:06:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes a good New Year's dream?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.01,0:06:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say the three luckiest things to see in your dreams are, \Nin order: Mt. Fuji, a hawk, and an eggplant.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.06,0:06:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so lucky.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.10,0:06:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so lucky!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.14,0:06:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Scary... So scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.77,0:06:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never had such a terrifying dream in my whole life!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.52,0:06:18.02,Alt,,0,0,0,,Terrifying?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:18.02,0:06:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all really good omens!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.40,0:06:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got Mt. Fuji, a hawk, an eggplant...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.99,0:06:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.19,0:06:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Even in a dream, it's too unrealistic for Mt. Fuji, \Na hawk, and an eggplant to appear together!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.95,0:06:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.62,0:06:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...what you mean.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.49,0:06:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Intermission!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.41,0:06:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.91,0:06:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}She's right. She was never gonna buy that \Nall three would appear in a dream at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.58,0:06:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I've never had a New Year's dream \Nwith those three things in it!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.05,0:06:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt anybody has.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:40.42,0:06:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If there are only three signs, you could go \Nyour whole life without having a lucky dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.97,0:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the plan?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.89,0:06:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We should start at fourth place \Nand do the top ten!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.01,0:06:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What could possibly be worse than an eggplant?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.89,0:06:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one thing it can be.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.31,0:06:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Time for the second act!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.85,0:06:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Continuing from number three, eggplant...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.27,0:06:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Four: green pepper!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.61,0:07:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Five: carrot!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.69,0:07:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Six: broccoli!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.69,0:07:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a list of all the veggies you hate!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.78,0:07:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Grow up, you toddler!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.03,0:07:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it went fan, tobacco, blind masseur...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.83,0:07:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.50,0:07:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}A fan spreads out wide, and the smoke \Nfrom tobacco rises up like your fortunes.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:21.17,0:07:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blind masseur?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.21,0:07:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Because he has no hair, not a hair \Non your head will be harmed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.97,0:07:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.42,0:07:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So what are we going to do next?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.26,0:07:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We went from animals to plants, \Nso next we need something even lower than that.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.93,0:07:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:35.10,0:07:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just gonna borrow your belt!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.44,0:07:37.40,Alt,,0,0,0,,Nooo!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.69,0:07:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Following on from broccoli...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.11,0:07:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven: chloroplasts!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.98,0:07:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight: mitochondria!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.99,0:07:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine: nuclei!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.74,0:07:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten: Golgi apparatus!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.61,0:07:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so lucky! So lucky!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:50.37,0:07:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.95,0:07:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm going to get sick!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.33,0:07:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what should we do?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.08,0:07:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Below a cell comes...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.42,0:08:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eleven: vanadium!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.21,0:08:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve: calcium!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.55,0:08:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirteen: potassium!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.05,0:08:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this seems really nice and healthy!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.93,0:08:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourteen: caesium!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.59,0:08:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen: strontium!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.43,0:08:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sixteen: plutonium!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.31,0:08:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You wanna see \Nwhat comes after sixteen?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.02,0:08:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.28,0:08:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you up to, Marii?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.78,0:08:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:31.66,0:08:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In you go, then. Into Almond!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:34.70,0:08:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so pink, though. It's embarrassing!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.46,0:08:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.75,0:08:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You can't come to Roppongi \Nand not go to Almond!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.83,0:08:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The pink symbolises colour blooming \Nin the heart of the barren city!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:43.79,0:08:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they chose it!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.01,0:08:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is... Is that true?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.76,0:08:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, maybe.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:49.22,0:08:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Almond was the first place in Japan \Nto give out warm towels to customers.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:52.93,0:08:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Precisely! This is the birthplace of \None of Japan's greatest dining traditions!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.64,0:09:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.69,0:09:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we just go in already?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.15,0:09:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.81,0:09:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry we're late!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.61,0:09:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all here. Shall we head out?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.03,0:09:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,After all that, we're not going in?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:11.36,0:09:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.53,0:09:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's huge!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten metres tall.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.41,0:09:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a spider?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.25,0:09:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got a name, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.91,0:09:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She does?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.25,0:09:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She's called Maman.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.88,0:09:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Maman?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.88,0:09:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand directly underneath her.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.01,0:09:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She's carrying eggs in that sac beneath her abdomen.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.64,0:09:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}This is a famous Roppongi meeting place, \Nlike Hachiko in Shibuya.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.85,0:09:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Meeting beneath Maman's egg sac... \NThat's horrifying...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:39.89,0:09:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.77,0:09:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting for someone under that? No way.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.06,0:09:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}If you waited an hour, maybe the eggs \Nwould hatch on top of you!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.57,0:09:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, you lot. It's art! Art!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.28,0:09:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there anything prettier?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.99,0:09:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is huge, too!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.87,0:09:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This one is five metres tall.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.79,0:10:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rose, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.75,0:10:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}This rose is a symbol of \Nthe love and beauty of 66 Plaza.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.17,0:10:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks more lethal than beautiful.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.59,0:10:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it might attack at any moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.05,0:10:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Reminds me of Little Shop of Horrors.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.76,0:10:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Feed me!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.10,0:10:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Argh! It's {\i1}art{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.81,0:10:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish they'd put up some {\i1}nice{\i0} art.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.60,0:10:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very least, something not terrifying.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.06,0:10:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is "Counter Void".
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.57,0:10:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just numbers. Not scary at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.57,0:10:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Four, four, four, four, four, four!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:35.24,0:10:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We're done four!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.49,0:10:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I changed my mind!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.37,0:10:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought four stood for "fourtunate"!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.91,0:10:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Roppongi Hills turned out to be pretty terrifying.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.83,0:10:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a lot to take in.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.00,0:10:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Like that building over there. \NWho knows what horrors it sees every day!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.50,0:10:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}All that happens is that \Na work of art watches over the area.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.09,0:10:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a mushroom?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.09,0:10:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks more like some kinda fruit.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.05,0:11:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the head of a really big person.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:00.68,0:11:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Guardian Stone.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.93,0:11:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Guardian Stone?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.23,0:11:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A watchman who safeguards Roppongi Hills.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.31,0:11:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look like it's guarding anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think Roppongi Hills is very well-protected.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.69,0:11:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Well, thanks to this stone, \NTV Asahi became the most-viewed TV station.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.37,0:11:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Doubt that stone's the reason.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.91,0:11:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew, at last we stopped somewhere relaxing.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.62,0:11:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, rice fish!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.33,0:11:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They're extraterrestrial life forms.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:30.09,0:11:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.84,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're space rice fish.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.26,0:11:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.97,0:11:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They're descended from rice fish \Nthat were born in space
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.89,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}as part of experiments carried out on board \Nthe space shuttle Columbia by Mukai Chiaki.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.18,0:11:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Rice fish born in space?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.93,0:11:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Oh yeah, they were the first vertebrates \Nto give birth in space.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.40,0:11:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Yep, and then they were released into \Nthis lake by the astronaut Mohri.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.11,0:11:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! Cute!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.49,0:11:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So they have spot-billed ducks here, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.95,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so peaceful here.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.07,0:12:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, the spot-bills tend to eat the rice fish.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.45,0:12:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's apparently taken quite a toll on their numbers.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.83,0:12:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The ducks eat the space fish...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.17,0:12:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But the ducks have to care for their ducklings...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.55,0:12:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks like the crows prey upon those ducklings.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.09,0:12:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk about the law of the jungle!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.88,0:12:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew Roppongi Hills was scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.14,0:12:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Tokyo recently passed city ordinance \Nto exterminate the crows.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.10,0:12:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So the top of the food chain is city ordinance?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.69,0:12:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,City ordinance is scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.44,0:12:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Since they built Roppongi Hills,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:34.19,0:12:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and Midtown,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.69,0:12:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Roppongi's changed beyond recognition.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.95,0:12:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where Velfarre used to be.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:43.16,0:12:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's called "Nicofarre".
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.91,0:12:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Wow! Sooner or later, Roppongi Hills \Nwill be called Nico Hills!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.12,0:12:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They should build a theatre called Nicohirotei, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.59,0:12:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They say the name Velfarre comes from \Na mix of Versace, Ferrari, and Armani.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.17,0:13:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the days of the Economic Bubble.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.84,0:13:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what it was like!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.89,0:13:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I bet you'd have been all over it \Nif you'd been in your twenties back then, Marii.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.68,0:13:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.98,0:13:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I kinda wanna go back to those bubbly days.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.85,0:13:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Take me back to the bubble age!", huh? Okay then.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.32,0:13:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Now hold on a sec!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.24,0:13:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a time machine!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.28,0:13:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoichoi Productions use it to wind the clock back.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.66,0:13:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Put on this swimsuit and get inside!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.58,0:13:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who am I, Hirosue Ryouko?!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.95,0:13:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,See you soon, Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:29.75,0:13:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go dancing for us!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:31.25,0:13:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.67,0:13:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Bubble!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.63,0:13:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna go bald!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.05,0:13:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.27,0:13:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is... the Bubble Era!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.36,0:14:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's pumping! The whole club is pumping!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.07,0:14:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dance like nobody's watching! Hoo hah!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.08,0:14:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.00,0:14:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is the Giroppon life!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.67,0:14:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Fetch me more pink Dom Pérignon!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.13,0:14:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse to stay anywhere but the Akasaka Prince!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.60,0:14:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Everyone is just bubbles...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.52,0:14:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thought we'd lost you for a second there, Marii!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.94,0:14:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.11,0:14:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Roppongi! Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.82,0:14:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Roppongi... in the present?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.78,0:14:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, what's this? More art?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.16,0:14:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. The title of this piece of public art is "Day Tripper".
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.08,0:14:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Day Tripper...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:54.50,0:14:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was all a bubble-like dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:58.88,0:15:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess all bubbles have to burst eventually.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.96,0:15:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Boris Vian, who wrote \N"Froth on the Daydream", once said:
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.13,0:15:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"There are only two things: \NLove, all sorts of love, with pretty girls,"
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.06,0:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}"and the music of New Orleans or Duke Ellington. \NEverything else ought to go,"
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.94,0:15:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"because everything else is ugly."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.61,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Shall we go on a pilgrimage \Nbefore we head home?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.24,0:15:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be a bit of a walk.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.99,0:15:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A pilgrimage?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:29.58,0:15:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,An Ebi** pilgrimage!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.03,0:15:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that building!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.66,0:15:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go drink tequila from ashtrays!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.50,0:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure we'll become national treasures like him.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.55,0:15:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"That ninja fella over there looks pretty hot."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.85,0:15:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"I went over there just now to ask him somethin'."
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.31,0:15:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,"What didja ask him?"
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.19,0:16:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"I asked if he's {\i1}shuriken{\i0} handle this heat!"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.73,0:16:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your continued appreciation.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.24,0:16:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't "Cool Biz"-themed, it's ninja-themed!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.75,0:16:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That's right! Backstage, \Nwe're already playing at being ninjas!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.38,0:16:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't get me!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.71,0:16:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down! It's too hot for this!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.34,0:16:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this dumb ninja game!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.18,0:16:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.39,0:16:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you to stop it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.19,0:16:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The iron rings, beloved of kunoichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.02,0:16:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.48,0:16:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the true weapon of the kunoichi is—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.69,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you okay?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.78,0:16:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Our feminine wiles!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.91,0:16:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I let my guard down...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.24,0:16:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this bullshit already!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.50,0:16:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.75,0:17:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You can't make us do Cool Biz \Nand then also stop us from playing ninja!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.00,0:17:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Do you think anybody would guess \Nwe were Cool Biz rakugo performers?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.01,0:17:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}You could survey one hundred dudes at Shinbashi \Nand they'd all say we were ninjas!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.26,0:17:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It doesn't matter how much we talk \Nabout saving electricity or Cool Biz.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.47,0:17:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The fact remains that performing \Non stage like this is weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.73,0:17:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}As rakugo performers, we should use \Nour stories to bring chills to people.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.44,0:17:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:24.11,0:17:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.02,0:17:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ghost stories!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.86,0:17:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.73,0:17:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We'll use spine-tingling tales \Nto bring chills to our audience.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.57,0:17:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ghost stories... Ghost stories, you say...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.24,0:17:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I wonder if ghosts are enough \Nto scare audiences nowadays.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.58,0:17:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so scary!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.46,0:17:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Sure they are, but nowadays \NI'd wager reality is even scarier.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.55,0:17:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.34,0:17:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the beach!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.38,0:17:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish that was me!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.51,0:17:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.17,0:17:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.26,0:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the background, a pale figure is staring at her.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.14,0:17:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh! Is it a ghost?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.22,0:17:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's super creepy!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.10,0:18:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be scary if it was a ghost,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.56,0:18:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but take a closer look.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.94,0:18:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing more than a person wearing a white outfit.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.77,0:18:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.77,0:18:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's human!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.24,0:18:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's even worse!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.11,0:18:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.32,0:18:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's creepy to catch a ghost on camera, \Nbut it's even creepier to catch a human dressed in white.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.29,0:18:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}That's true. A ghost you can see is less terrifying \Nthan radioactive materials you can't.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.00,0:18:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ghosts are still scary, though!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.08,0:18:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Do you know the story of \Nthe red-roofed apartment on 3rd Street?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.88,0:18:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the one nobody can move into?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.38,0:18:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She never leaves...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.22,0:18:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}No matter how much they exorcise the place, \Nthe sitting ghost never leaves, bound to that spot!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.10,0:18:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that scary?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.26,0:18:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Bound spirits are pretty scary,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.31,0:18:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but look at this photograph.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.60,0:18:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A spirit bound to an old house?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.94,0:18:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closer.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:49.11,0:18:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Looks like a monster that'd \Nshow up in the Cthulhu Mythos. {alt: Looks almost like some Lovecraftian horror.}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.78,0:18:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Look even closer.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.74,0:18:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}It's actually the politician \Nthat everyone says looks like a fish.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.78,0:18:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, that guy.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.99,0:19:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How can one person mess up so much?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.12,0:19:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, this isn't a house. It's parliament.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.95,0:19:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}A politician who raises consumption tax \Nis more terrifying than any ghost could ever be, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.00,0:19:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They are! They can't even compare!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.59,0:19:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's scarier because it hurts everyone in the country.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.88,0:19:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I still think ghosts are scarier!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:15.09,0:19:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something happen to you?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.30,0:19:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}The other day, when I was walking down \Nthe corridor to the dressing room...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.52,0:19:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}A sudden, unearthly rapping! \NIt scared me to death!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.31,0:19:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing scary about that.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.40,0:19:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.28,0:19:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget a sudden, unearthly rapping.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.41,0:19:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is far scarier: ubiquitous, un-Japanese pop.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.74,0:19:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But music from that country is really popular.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:43.66,0:19:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Has anyone here actually bought a CD from there?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.16,0:19:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.87,0:19:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.29,0:19:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.13,0:19:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.25,0:19:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Terrifying!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.09,0:19:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How can it be popular if nobody's buying CDs?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.71,0:19:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try a visual approach.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:56.13,0:19:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If we paint the room blue, it'll feel cooler in here.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.47,0:20:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}We can experiment in here, and if it works, \Nwe can paint the whole theatre.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.52,0:20:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.43,0:20:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:05.23,0:20:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I don't think they'll let us—
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.19,0:20:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The dragonfly's glasses are as blue as the sky...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.49,0:20:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mariiemon!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.57,0:20:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She crashed like an Osprey!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.08,0:20:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks more like a member of the Blue Man Group.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.87,0:20:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The Blue Man Group has three members!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.67,0:20:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if this'll pull in more guests.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.08,0:20:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.59,0:20:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I do think it feels a little cooler now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.05,0:20:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we're used to it...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.22,0:20:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hot again...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.39,0:20:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need more blue stuff.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.10,0:20:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all dye our hair blue!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.31,0:20:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we, an anime from the 80s?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.40,0:20:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not Konata! {Lucky Star}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.48,0:20:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not Ayanami! {Evangelion}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.69,0:20:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not Lord Aoshi! {Rurouni Kenshin?}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.61,0:20:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not Soldier Blue! {Terra e?}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:57.82,0:21:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really feeling that generation gap here.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.70,0:21:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are remakes and re-runs.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.08,0:21:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just give it a go.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.79,0:21:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Lining our blue heads up like this \Nmakes things feel a little fresher in here.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:11.37,0:21:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It works much better than I expected.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.25,0:21:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}They should stop re-airing Touch during summer break \Nand only show anime with blue-haired characters!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.38,0:21:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.47,0:21:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hot again now that we're used to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.18,0:21:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should wear blue kimono.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.52,0:21:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Everyone wear blue!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.98,0:21:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh, this kinda works!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:34.61,0:21:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.98,0:21:40.11,Default,,0,0,23,,I just had another great idea!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.87,0:21:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ghosts!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.03,0:21:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that about?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.91,0:21:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,His wife's way scarier than any ghosts.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:50.54,0:21:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already grown used to this, too. It's so hot.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:54.29,0:21:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else! We need more blue!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:56.88,0:21:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.22,0:22:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now {\i1}that's{\i0} refreshing!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.68,0:22:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfect thing for summer.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:04.51,0:22:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Marii's Mongolian Spot is so blue!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.18,0:22:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At least my butt is cool!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.27,0:23:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Bouhatei Tetora here!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.73,0:23:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Anrakutei Kukuru here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.49,0:23:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuurubiyuutei Gankyou here.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.20,0:23:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Haroukitei Kigurumi here!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:47.99,0:23:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Buratei Marii here!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.74,0:23:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The conversations in this anime...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.45,0:23:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...are written to be as inoffensive as possible...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.00,0:23:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...so as not to interfere with your enjoyment...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:56.79,0:23:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...of viewing cute gi...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.63,0:23:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...rls.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.38,0:24:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The splendid beauty of the thirteenth episode contains:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.75,0:24:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"Character Assassination".
Dialogue: 10,0:24:02.84,0:24:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"Akihabubble".
Dialogue: 10,0:24:03.92,0:24:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And "A Little Ex..."
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.22,0:24:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,"...tra".
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.80,0:24:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Hey, wait a sec! Why do I always \Nget stuck with the very end?!
